<SECTION>  Sports  </SECTION>
<HEADLINE>  BLOCKBUSTER BOWL AT A GLANCE
ALABAMA VS. COLORADO  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>  RECORDS: No. 8 Alabama of the Southeastern Conference is 10-1; No. 15 Colorado
of the Big Eight Conference is 8-2-1. Alabama has faced Colorado only once,
losing 47-33 in the 1969 Liberty Bowl. Alabama lost to Louisville 34-7 in the
1991 Fiesta Bowl. Colorado beat Notre Dame 10-9 in the 1991 Orange Bowl.;
LINE: The game is rated even.; WHAT TO WATCH FOR: Alabama ranks eighth in the
NCAA in rushing, averaging 252 yards. RB Siran Stacy is the workhorse for the
Crimson Tide with 966 yards in 200 carries and has scored 10 touchdowns.
Colorado's high-powered offense is directed by QB Darian Hagan, who has
completed 88 of 170 passes for 1,228 yards and 12 TDs. Hagan also has rushed
for 386 yards in 133 carries and scored three TDs.  </TEXT>
